    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-09-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-09-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="288"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d288">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.7353b W 52/38</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Portugal</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dearing</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lisbon</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-09-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 15, 1922</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received September 30.]</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 106</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform the Department that
                    the Portuguese Parliament brought its session to a close about 2 o’clock this
                        [<hi rend="italic">yesterday?</hi>] morning. I sent the Department a
                    telegram No. 92, September 14th,<note n="97" xml:id="d288fn97">Not
                        printed.</note> to this effect.</p>
                <p>The Western Union Telegraph Company’s petition for the elimination of the
                    objectionable amendment inserted in the Chamber of Deputies in the definitive
                    contract, did not come out of the Senate Finance Committee and will still have
                    to be acted upon by that Committee when Parliament reconvenes on the 23rd of
                    October.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fred Morris Dearing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
